💡 PRO TIPS FOR WINDOWS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. USE WINDOWS TERMINAL
   - Better than regular PowerShell
   - Get it from Microsoft Store (free)
   - Supports tabs, colors, etc.

2. CREATE A DESKTOP SHORTCUT
   - Right-click start_server.bat
   - Send to > Desktop (create shortcut)
   - Rename to "Contract Tool"
   - Now you can start with one click!

3. AUTO-START ON WINDOWS BOOT (Optional)
   - Press Win+R
   - Type: shell:startup
   - Copy start_server.bat shortcut there
   - Server starts when Windows starts!

4. KEEP TERMINAL OPEN
   - Server needs to run continuously
   - Don't close the PowerShell window
   - Minimize it instead

5. TEST LOCALLY FIRST
   - Always test on localhost:5000
   - Fix any issues before sharing
   - Then share your network IP with others

